The critical constraint is temporal, not coding: after `stake()`, this bug only pays if some reward accrual happens in a later block timestamp. I’m structuring the verifier as a state machine so it uses direct verifier-held JUICE first, stakes with the oversized `stakeWeek`, and then on a later call realizes the inflated claim once the forked test advances time or block state.
